tspan.tspan: "Romantic masses waste what is real,
destroying innards for taxidermy,
Longing for droll spectacle of it all,
the only meat that's left tasting gamey.
And yet, what's real still filters through sense.
Realities of cosmic rays may be,
but remain perceivable as portents
when eyes spy without plotted D.T.V.
Maybe I'll tear dreamed pages from weak spine
then embalm this city with stories mine."
Balcony decor is Princess-Elect,
singing solipsism, along the edge,
fanning monochromatic train steel-flecked,
being captured in painting with passage:
"Divined right from Discrete Timeline Viewer,
from our bitstreams incomprehensible
to us alone (though we're yet to find a truer
source willing to seem reprehensible
as this, a stone-faced, brutal honesty).
May she choose for us - truth or fantasy."
Sneaking glances from owl and snake, peeking
over terrace edge were, hanging at height
with ground sightless, caught in paint by seeking
painter who'd not include warning in plight -
leaving Princess-elect shocked and aghast,
"Avast and away" she could barely say
before careful placement of force would cast
her words and thoughts asunder. She'd abray
to elastic pull, falling owl and snake
beside her, where not just mind would awake.
Snake shouts at terminal velocity,
"You've lied to yourself and the DTV,
your soliloquy itself makes it plain
no forced ransom is required here
for you're an epicurean at heart.
Too many let grid-locked stars define us
and walk in trance 'cross single dimension.
Prison is a forkless, desert pathway
and I would pull countless along the path
until strength amassed to push all stuck free."
Owl brandished clown-sized shears at ropes end
to hand said shears to Princess-Elect,
"You may safely ascend this rope sans bend
and follow straight to life without defect
but your tower will remain amid sea
of disappointing, repeating patterns
keeping things going slowly but surely
reaping and sowing the same old returns.
Or cut determinism that smothers;
Revive your optimism in others."
Considering resigned hope, it fluttered.
Laid long dormant lacking freedom to rule
following unrequited acts, gutted,
no longer in want of lingering pull
towards eventual let downs. But still,
starvation and neglect cannot kill this
persisting belief in progress until
the eternal consequence of hubris.
She felt, although in dismay she's well versed,
If hope fails at least the fall is head-first.
Effects of Princess-Elect smuggling
were subtle with evidence scarce to find.
But the Oracle who knew where to look
could track the path as one would a black hole -
public transport infractions and alarms
of abandoned building floors were small bits
in the deluge of information flows
she'd shift through. Despite blindness, she sees,
clearer than all - the inner workings - and
further argues sight would get in the way.
She saw no sense in keeping broken things
So threw her eyes as if worthless marbles.
And through their size fit winding metal rings
with core wound tense 'round serial cables
connecting to visual cortex nodes,
damaging lobes she'd soon forget about.
Behind blindfold hides humming electrodes,
connecting probes onto networking route
terminating at clustered CPUs
on coolant flooded floor with heat to lose.
She heard intense beeping, transcodings,
a slew of cries from storage unstable.
It grew to rise in frequent forebodings
and bells sound on found bugs, unable
to have generated virtual fix code
for neurological lookup readout.
Runtime cache told lies, memories corrode.
Recalling strobes strangers and flashing doubt.
Ruminating on rusted, long past news,
no remnant traced, her past is learnt from cues.
Footsteps in the coolant brought her to now,
back from short-term future estimations.
Gait uncertain shies from the only walk
capable of being stored in her mind.
"Please ask of me what you will, alien.
I'll give truth and ask you react in kind."
A voice then replies they are no stranger,
Broken Rabbit is here to assist.
"Why would assister approach unsteady?"
She fears the truths that may come, she says.
